{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"806f9ffa-317e-4d68-82b1-9f3f23833c89","content":"I don't see a `.dmp` file in the current directory. To help you analyze it, here's what I need:\n\n1. **Upload or provide the path** to your `.dmp` file so I can access it.\n\n2. **Recommended tools** for .NET crash dump analysis:\n   - **`dotnet-dump analyze`** — the best cross-platform option for .NET dumps. Install with:\n     ```\n     dotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\n     ```\n   - **WinDbg + SOS** — if you're on Windows.\n\n3. **Key commands** once loaded (`dotnet-dump analyze <file.dmp>`):\n   | Command | Purpose |\n   |---|---|\n   | `clrstack` | Managed call stack of crashing thread |\n   | `pe` (PrintException) | Last exception details + stack trace |\n   | `clrthreads` | List all managed threads |\n   | `dumpheap -stat` | Heap summary (for OOM crashes) |\n   | `setthread <id>` + `clrstack` | Inspect specific threads |\n\n**Could you upload or specify the path to your `.dmp` file?** I can then walk through the analysis with you directly.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"65848b9f-861d-4033-a863-783afeab9fb5","outputTokens":291,"requestId":"7640:2D289A:E70D55:10EEB20:69FE93ED"},"id":"5fcb2cd7-d48d-45a1-a515-a054abb3eac2","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:55:02.542Z","parentId":"997e04bb-6730-4728-924b-1895ba7eea0c"}
